quoted_text: From the 49ers, rookie Trey Sermon is a healthy scratch today and COVID is not an issue. Remember, he was essentially the team's No. 2 running back from OTAs onward. It will be interesting to hear what Kyle Shanahan says after the game.

text:
The Vikings used 11 personnel (3 WRs, 1 RB, 1 TE) more than any other formation yesterday -- 32 of 75 plays.

That might be in part because they trailed in the second half, but it's worth noting after Mike Zimmer mentioned they'd use it more after Irv Smith's injury.
